step_data.thought: Based on the accessibility tree, I can see that I'm already on the CMS Blocks section page. The URL in the RootWebArea shows 'http://127.0.0.1:7780/admin/cms/block/' and the heading shows 'Blocks'. The page displays a list of all CMS blocks in a table with columns for ID, Title, Identifier, Store View, Status, Created, Modified, and Action. There are 18 blocks listed, and I can see options to add a new block, search, filter, and perform actions on selected blocks. Since I've successfully accessed the CMS Blocks section as requested in the goal, I should inform the user that we've completed the task.
step_data.action: stop('You are now in the CMS Blocks section. This page displays all your content blocks with their details including ID, title, identifier, status, and creation/modification dates. From here, you can edit existing blocks by clicking the Select button next to any block, or create a new block using the "Add New Block" button at the top of the page.')
